uestions   Common Questions   Where are recharging stations located?  What kind of devices am I able to recharge?  What do I do if my recharge locker won’t open?  More…            Features       Recharge stations are available to individually store, charge and secure phones, tablets, iPads, and laptops  Easy to use and works just like a hotel safe  Each locker comes with digital locks for individual, 24/7 use  Recharging options exist for a variety of cables and power needs  Options depend on location and recharge stations availability              More Info   Applicability  Please be aware of the hours of operation for the location you are charging your device. If it is left overnight, you will not be able to retrieve the device until the next day. Recharge stations are located at:   Behavioral Sciences Building Learning Center  Student Center East Tower 401 computer lab  University Hall 2nd floor Port Center               Google Maps image     LTS Support Office   806 South Halsted Street,  Lecture Center E, room E112,  Chicago,  IL    Phone: 312-413-0003, Option 1  Website: https://accc.uic.edu/support         Service Level Agreement       Service Request Fulfillment Time  Locker Access: Immediate, Questions: 2 business days    Incident Resolution Time  Forgotten code: 1 business day    Service Availability  Available during the times hosting locations are open (varies by location)    Maintenance Window(s)  N/A    Service Notification Channel(s)  ACCC Service Notices    Reviewed to Ensure SLA Meets Business Requirements  Provisional SLA    Date Reviewed  Provisional SLA    Service owner: Elizabeth Romero Fuerte               Services    Back to main content           Communication and Collaboration     Cloud Storage     Box    Google Drive    OneDrive      Conferencing     Blackboard Collaborate    Google Meet    Webex Meetings    Zoom      Digital Signage     Industry Weapon      Email and Calendaring     Exchange    Gmail    Google Calendar    Listserv      Eme